      <div class="container">
        <div class="row x_space">
          <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h2 style="padding-bottom: 30px;">Privacy Policy </h2>
    <h3>Zebu Privacy Policy Information</h3>

      <p>Zebu Infrastructure Online respects the privacy of everyone who visits this site.  Unlike other sites we <strong>WILL NOT</strong> SELL, LEND, OR GIVE AWAY YOUR INFORMATION TO ANY THIRD PARTY!</p>
      
      <p>Please read our Privacy Policy carefully so that you can understand how we collect, we use and we <strong>DO NOT</strong> disclose any of the information that you provide to us.</p>
      
      <p>By accessing this Website you accept all the terms and conditions of this Privacy Policy.  In particular, by submitting your personal information to us, you will be deemed to have given your permission for internal use only, but NOT to disclose it.</p>
      <h3>Privacy Policy Coverage</h3>
      
      <p>This Privacy Policy covers our use, but not any disclosure, of your personal information, which this Website might collect.  For the purposes of this Privacy Policy, "this Website" means all the web pages related to the <strong>Zebu.io</strong> site, which excludes all links to third party sites.</p>

      <h3>Responsibility Personal Information Collected on this Website</h3>
      
      <p>Zebu Infrastructure Online controls the personal data collected on this Website.</p>
      
      <h3>Underage Notice â€“ Visitors Under 18 Years Old</h3>
      <p>This site does not intentionally collect personal data of persons under 18 years old.  If you are under 18 years old please do not send us your personal information (for example, your name, address and email address).  Individuals under 18 years old shall not post any personal information to this site.</p>
      
       <h3>Information Collection and Use</h3>
       
      <p>We collect and use personal information (including name, address, telephone number and email address) in order to:</p>
      
   
      <ul>
      
      <li>Respond to queries or requests submitted by you</li>
      <li>Process orders or applications submitted by you</li>
      <li>Carry out obligations in relation to any agreement you have with us</li>
      <li>Resolve problems with any products or services supplied to you</li>
      <li>Informing you about products and service updates.  This may include contacting you by e-mail or other means.</li>
      </ul>

      
      <h3>Third Parties</h3>
      <p>We may eventually use third parties for the fulfilment of our obligations hereunder.  However, except as set out in this Privacy Policy, we will not disclose any personally identifiable information without your permission, unless forced by court orders.  Or if we believe that such action is necessary to protect and/or defend our rights, property or personal safety.</p>
      
      <p>We cannot be responsible for the privacy policies and practices of other websites even if you:</p>
      
  
      <ul>
      <li>Accessed the third party website using links from our Website; or</li>
	  <li>Linked to our Website from a third party website.</li>
      </ul>

     
      <p>We recommend that you check the policy of each site you visit and contact the owner or operator of such website if you have any concerns or questions.  Unlike other sites, we will NOT use information for purposes other than as defined in this Privacy Policy.</p>
      
      <p>Additionally, if at any time you wish us to stop using your information for any or all of the below purposes, please let us know (see contact information below).  We will take the necessary steps to stop the use of your information for such purposes with immediate effect.</p>
      
       <h3>Collection of Non-Personal information</h3>
      <p>This site may automatically collect non-personal information about you, such as the type of internet browsers you use or the website from which you linked to our Website.  We may also aggregate details which you have submitted to the Website (for example, your age and the town where you live).  You cannot be identified from this information and it is only used to improve service on this web site.</p>
      
      <p>We will NOT supply third parties with this non-personal or aggregated data for uses in connection with this Website.</p>
      
      <p>This site may store some information, known as a "cookie", on your computer when you look at our Website.  The type of information is a result of your browser accepting a cookie, which is specific to your PC and includes the IP address, the date and time the PC visited the Website, what parts of our Website visited and whether the web pages requests are successfully delivered.  This information is anonymous; it represents a computer rather than a person.  We use the cookie information to improve our knowledge of the use of our Website.  This allows us to enhance our web offerings to clients and to provide a better online experience.</p>
      
      <p>You can erase or block this information by changing the settings on your computer (please refer to your help screens or manuals).  If you do erase or block this information you may not be able to utilize some features of the Website.</p>
	  
	   <h3>Google User Data </h3>
      
      <p>We do not collect or store any information related to the user, we only transmit the session token to the client. As such we do not use any information and we do not share any information with third parties.</p>
      
      <h3>E-mail and Feedback Forms</h3>
      
      <p>If at any time this Website offers any e-mail, feedback or forum facilities, we may collect the information, which you disclose.  Such information will follow the terms in this Privacy Policy.</p>
      
      <h3>Security of Personal Data</h3>
      
      <p>We have implemented technology and policies with the objective of protecting your privacy from unauthorized access and we will update these measures as new technology becomes available, as appropriate.</p>
      
      <h3>Privacy Policy Changes</h3>
      
      <p>This Privacy Policy may change over time.  Please check our Privacy Policy on a regular basis.  Note that we will NOT change this Privacy Policy in a way to disclose your data.</p>
      
       
